parameterdescription.para: Value to write.
Target of write.
Write position. Writing will begin at this position in the buffer.
Number of lower order bits to copy from source to target buffer.

memberdef.argsstring: (this ulong value, int bits, ref int bitposition)
memberdef.name: Extract

briefdescription.para: Extract (read/deserialize) a value from a source primitive (the buffer) by reading x bits starting at the bitposition, and return the reconstructed value.

parameterdescription.para: Source primitive buffer to read from.
Number of lower order bits to copy from source to return value.
Auto-incremented reference to the value read bit pointer. Extraction starts at this point in value.

simplesect.para: Downcast this ulong return value to the desired type.

memberdef.argsstring: (this ulong value, ref int bitposition, int bits)

Auto-incremented read position for the buffer (in bits)
